# Frontend Next.js Rules
- Use the App Router for all Next.js applications.
- Use Tailwind CSS and shared UI primitives; use shadcn/ui patterns consistently where adopted.
- Design mobile-first, responsive layouts with clear empty, loading, error, and success states.
- Keep data fetching patterns consistent; isolate API clients and avoid duplicating request logic.
- Customer web prioritizes visual quality, discovery, conversion, and SEO.
- Admin prioritizes operational clarity, dense information, and safe workflows.
- Courier prioritizes speed, legibility, large touch targets, and minimal interaction cost.
